The paper discusses clustering algorithms and their performance on high-dimensional data sets. This topic falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and databases (cs.DB). Given that the paper focuses on learning models from data, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses data sets and their properties, cs.DM and cs.DB are also likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper deals with clustering algorithms, which are often used in natural language processing, cs.CL is a possible sub-category as well.
